    • Method Detail

      • destroy

        public void destroy()
        Destroys the object correctly.
        Description:
        This method destroys the instance of FunctionUnitBase in the native library.
        It is mandatory to call this method to clean the allocated memory in the native library, but
        if the method deleteChild is used, then destroy is called internally for all listed childs.
        The Function Unit object that act as a root must always be cleared with destroy.
        TIP: use destroy only for the root Function Unit. This destroys the complete tree structure.

      • addChild

        public int addChild(int outputNo,
                    int type)
             throws FeException
        Adds a Function Unit to the child list.
        Parameters:
        outputNo - the output number where the Function Unit is physically connected
        type - Function Unit type identifier (TYPE_HF_MUX, TYPE_HF_DAT, TYPE_UHF_MUX) for the child
        Returns:
        status
        • 0 if OK
        Throws:
        FeException - exception with error code (<0)

        Description:
        This method adds a Function Unit to the child list.
        With this method, one can build a tree structure, which represents the physical connections
        of function units. Only multiplexers can have 1..8 childs. Dynamic antenna tuners represents an
        endpoint of a tree and can't have childs. This method can throw a FedmException, if an error occurs inside the Java Native Interface.

      • deleteChild

        public int deleteChild(int outputNo)
                throws FeException
        Deletes a Function Unit from the child list.
        Parameters:
        outputNo - the output number where the Function Unit is physically connected
        Returns:
        status
        • 0 if OK
        Throws:
        FeException - exception with error code (<0)

        Description:
        This method deletes a Function Unit from the child list.
        All childs of the Function Unit will be deleted too.

      • deleteChildList

        public int deleteChildList()
        Deletes the complete child list.

        • 0 if OK

      • getChild

        public FunctionUnitBase getChild(int outputNo)
                          throws FeException
        Returns a Function Unit from the child list.
        Parameters:
        outputNo - the output number where the Function Unit is physically connected
        Returns:
        child object
        Throws:
        FeException - exception with error code (<0)
        Description:
        This method returns a Function Unit from the child list.
        If no child is listed for this output number, ErrorCode.NO_DATA is thrown.
